{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Now I understand the situation. The FC41DAAR03A09 firmware's `+QBLESCAN` URCs don't include advertising data, so names aren't in the scan payload. To get device names I need to GATT-connect after the scan and read the Device Name characteristic (Generic Access service, handle 0x0003).", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:40:03+00:00", "time": "23:40:03"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Plan:", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:40:03+00:00", "time": "23:40:03"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "1. Add `FC41D_BLE_GetName()` to `fc41d.c` — connects, reads handle 3, disconnects", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:40:03+00:00", "time": "23:40:03"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "2. Expose it in `fc41d.h`", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:40:03+00:00", "time": "23:40:03"}
