{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "The GATT flow shows the issue clearly:", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:43:10+00:00", "time": "23:43:10"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "- **Device 1**: `AT+QBLECONN` got `OK` but the `+QBLECONN:0,0` URC never arrived (connection pending / timed out). We returned 0 **without disconnecting** → BLE stack left in \"connecting\" state.", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:43:10+00:00", "time": "23:43:10"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "- **Devices 2–4**: Got `ERROR` immediately because the module is still busy trying to connect to device 1.", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:43:10+00:00", "time": "23:43:10"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Fix: always call `AT+QBLEDISCONN=0` before returning on a connect-URC timeout.", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:43:10+00:00", "time": "23:43:10"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:43:13+00:00", "time": "23:43:13"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "  ▶ Edit  C:\\CCoreAI\\DirectClaude\\DirectClaude\\projects\\15-ble-scan\\Core\\Src\\fc41d.c", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:43:13+00:00", "time": "23:43:13"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Also handle the case where connect command returned `ERROR` — that means the stack refused the command. A brief re-init might unblock it for subsequent devices. Let me add a BLE reinit helper on ERROR:", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:43:16+00:00", "time": "23:43:16"}
