{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Here's what happened and where things stand:", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:47:49+00:00", "time": "23:47:49"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "**Code changes made:**", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:47:49+00:00", "time": "23:47:49"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "- `fc41d.h` — added `FC41D_BLE_GetName()` prototype", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:47:49+00:00", "time": "23:47:49"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "- `fc41d.c` — added `FC41D_BLE_GetName()`: connects via `AT+QBLECONN=0,<type>,<addr>`, waits for `+QBLECONN:0,0` URC, reads Device Name characteristic via `AT+QBLEGATTCRD=0,3,0`, parses `+QBLEGATTRD:` response (handles both hex-encoded and raw ASCII data), then disconnects", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:47:49+00:00", "time": "23:47:49"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "- `main.c` — GATT name resolution pass after scan, before final print", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:47:49+00:00", "time": "23:47:49"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "**Why names are empty today:**", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:47:49+00:00", "time": "23:47:49"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "All 4 nearby devices are phones/tablets with BLE privacy mode on. They advertise using **Resolvable Private Addresses** (type=1, rotating) and broadcast **non-connectable** advertising packets. The module can scan them (one-way) but cannot establish a GATT connection to read the Device Name characteristic.", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:47:49+00:00", "time": "23:47:49"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "**When it will work:**", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:47:49+00:00", "time": "23:47:49"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Bring any connectable BLE peripheral into range — an ESP32 dev board, nRF dongle, BLE HR monitor, temperature sensor, etc. — and you'll see the name in the final summary:", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:47:49+00:00", "time": "23:47:49"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "```", "ts": "2026-05-17T20:47:49+00:00", "time": "23:47:49"}
